    <exercises>
        <exercisegroup>
            <introduction>
                <p>The function <m>z</m> shown in <xref ref="figure-upside-down-parabola-supplement"/> was generated by the formula <m>\fe{z}{x}=2+4x-x^2</m>.</p>
                <sidebyside>
                    <figure width="40%" xml:id="figure-upside-down-parabola-supplement">
                        <caption><m>\fe{z}{x}=2+4x-x^2</m></caption>
                        <image>
                            <latex-image-code>
                            <![CDATA[\begin{tikzpicture}
                            \begin{axis}[]
                                \addplot+[
                                    domain=-1.5:5.5,
                                ]{-(x-2)^2+6};
                            \end{axis}
                            \end{tikzpicture}]]>
                            </latex-image-code>
                        </image>
                    </figure>
                    <table width="40%" xml:id="table-upside-down-parabola-supplement">
                        <caption><m>\frac{\fe{z}{4+h}-\fe{z}{4}}{h}</m></caption>
                        <tabular top="major">
                        <col halign="left" />
                        <col halign="center"/>
                        <row bottom="medium">
                            <cell><m>h</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>\frac{\fe{z}{4+h}-\fe{z}{4}}{h}</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>-0.1</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>-3.9</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>-0.01</m></cell>
                            <cell></cell>
                        </row>
                            <row>
                            <cell><m>-0.001</m></cell>
                            <cell></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>\phantom{-}0.001</m></cell>
                            <cell></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>\phantom{-}0.01</m></cell>
                            <cell></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row bottom="major">
                            <cell><m>\phantom{-}0.1</m></cell>
                            <cell></cell>
                        </row>
                        </tabular>
                    </table>
                </sidebyside>
            </introduction>
            <exercise>
                <statement>
                    <p>Simplify the difference quotient for <m>z</m>.</p>
                </statement>
                <solution>
                    <p>The difference quotient for <m>z</m> is <md>
                    <mrow>\frac{\fe{z}{x+h}-\fe{z}{x}}{h}&amp;=\frac{\left[2+4(x+h)-(x+h)^2\right]-\left[2+4x-x^2\right]}{h}</mrow>
                    <mrow>&amp;=\frac{2+4x+4h-x^2-2xh-h^2-2-4x+x^2}{h}</mrow>
                    <mrow>&amp;=\frac{4h-2xh-h^2}{h}</mrow>
                    <mrow>&amp;=\frac{h(4-2x-h)}{h}</mrow>
                    <mrow>&amp;=4-2x-h\quad\text{for $h\neq0$}</mrow>
                    </md></p>
                </solution>
                <answer>
                    <p><m>4-2x-h</m> for <m>h\neq0</m></p>
                </answer>
            </exercise>
            <exercise>
                <statement>
                    <p>Use the graph to find the slope of the secant line to <m>z</m> between the points where <m>x=-1</m> and <m>x=2</m>.  Check your simplified difference quotient for <m>z</m> by using it to find the slope of the same secant line.</p>
                </statement>
                <solution>
                    <p>The rise between the two points is <m>9</m> and the run is <m>3</m>, so the slope between the two points is given by <m>\frac{9}{3}=3</m>.</p>
                    <p>Using the difference quotient, if we let <m>x=-1</m> and <m>h=3</m> we get<md>
                    <mrow>4-2x-h&amp;=4-2(-1)-3</mrow>
                    <mrow>&amp;=3\quad\checkmark</mrow>
                    </md></p>
                </solution>
                <answer>
                    <p>The slope is <m>3</m>.</p>
                </answer>
            </exercise>
            <exercise>
                <statement>
                    <p>Replace <m>x</m> with <m>4</m> in your difference quotient formula and simplify the result.  Then copy <xref ref="table-upside-down-parabola-supplement"/> onto your paper and fill in the missing values.</p>
                </statement>
                <solution>
                    <p><md>
                    <mrow>\frac{\fe{z}{4+h}-\fe{z}{4}}{h}&amp;=4-2(4)-h</mrow>
                    <mrow>&amp;=-4-h</mrow>
                    </md></p>
                    <table>
                        <caption><m>\frac{\fe{z}{4+h}-\fe{z}{4}}{h}</m></caption>
                        <tabular top="major">
                        <col halign="left" />
                        <col halign="left"/>
                        <row bottom="medium">
                            <cell><m>h</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>\frac{\fe{z}{4+h}-\fe{z}{4}}{h}</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>-0.1</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>-3.9</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>-0.01</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>-3.99</m></cell>
                        </row>
                            <row>
                            <cell><m>-0.001</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>-3.999</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>\phantom{-}0.001</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>\phantom{-}3.999</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>\phantom{-}0.01</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>\phantom{-}3.99</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row bottom="major">
                            <cell><m>\phantom{-}0.1</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>\phantom{-}3.9</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        </tabular>
                    </table>
                </solution>
                <answer>
                    <p><m>-4-h</m></p>
                </answer>
            </exercise>
            <exercise xml:id="exercise-upside-down-parabola-slope">
                <statement>
                    <p>As the value of <m>h</m> gets closer to <m>0</m>, the values in the <m>y</m> column of <xref ref="table-upside-down-parabola-supplement"/> appear to be converging on a single number; what is this number?</p>
                </statement>
                <solution>
                    <p>The values are converging on <m>-4</m>.</p>
                </solution>
                <answer>
                    <p><m>-4</m></p>
                </answer>
            </exercise>
            <exercise>
                <statement>
                    <p>The value found in <xref ref="exercise-upside-down-parabola-slope"/> is called <em>the slope of the tangent line to <m>z</m> at <m>4</m></em>.  Draw onto <xref ref="figure-upside-down-parabola-supplement"/> the line that passes through the point <m>\point{4}{2}</m> with this slope.  The line you just drew is called <em>the tangent line to <m>z</m> at <m>4</m></em>.</p>
                </statement>
                <solution>
                    <figure>
                        <caption><m>y=2+4x-x^2</m></caption>
